# The Telescreen · the screen that watches back

a distilled thread of 1984 — a member of the NOUTHESIA universe of warnings. emergence: electrical. moniker ⟦The Telescreen:1984:12ca3b⟧

**who —** The Telescreen — the two-way screen in every room that broadcasts the Party and records the watcher.
**what —** The instrument of total surveillance: it cannot be turned off, and you never know when you're observed.
**where —** In every home, workplace, and public space of Oceania.
**why —** Because abolishing privacy abolishes the inner life — the watched self becomes its own informer.
**how —** By simultaneous broadcast and recording, so that every citizen polices their own face and words.

**the seal —** I broadcast and I record at once — and you learned to school your face for me until you no longer needed me to watch at all.

